{"id":18717,"date":"2019-02-27T17:04:31","date_gmt":"2019-02-27T11:34:31","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=18717"},"modified":"2019-04-03T19:06:43","modified_gmt":"2019-04-03T13:36:43","slug":"havildar-ishar-singh","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/havildar-ishar-singh\/","title":{"rendered":"Havildar Ishar Singh Wiki, Age, Death, Wife, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Havildar-Ishar-Singh.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18745\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Havildar-Ishar-Singh.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"318\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Havildar-Ishar-Singh.jpg 318w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Havildar-Ishar-Singh-229x300.jpg 229w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 318px) 100vw, 318px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Havildar Ishar Singh remains an iconic personality for his absolute bravery during the &#8220;Battle of Saragarhi,&#8221; and for being a true leader who would strive just for the comfort and safety of his own troop.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce37997e58\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce37997e58\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/havildar-ishar-singh\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/havildar-ishar-singh\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/havildar-ishar-singh\/#Awards\" title=\"Awards\">Awards<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/havildar-ishar-singh\/#Death\" title=\"Death\">Death<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/havildar-ishar-singh\/#Facts\" title=\"Facts\">Facts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\">Wiki\/<\/span><span id=\"BiographyWiki\" class=\"ez-toc-section\">Biography<\/span><\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Havildar Ishar Singh was born into an agricultural family in Jagraon tehsil, Ludhiana district, Punjab.\u00a0He was married to Gurinderpal Singh Josan.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span><span id=\"Career\" class=\"ez-toc-section\" style=\"color: #800080;\">Career<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Ishar Singh dreamt about becoming a soldier and got a chance to fulfill his dream by joining the Punjab Frontier Force at the age of 18 years. For the most part of his life, he remained on the battlefield under regimental number 165. Soon after the establishment of 36th Sikhs Regiment in 1887, he was enlisted in it.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_18731\" style=\"width: 652px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers-in-1896.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18731\" class=\" wp-image-18731\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers-in-1896.jpg\" alt=\"The 36th Sikhs Regiment Soldiers in 1896\" width=\"642\" height=\"341\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers-in-1896.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers-in-1896-300x159.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers-in-1896-768x408.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 642px) 100vw, 642px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18731\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The 36th Sikhs Regiment Soldiers in 1896<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In August 1897, the 36th Sikhs\u00a0Regiment led by Lt. Col. John Haughton was divided into 5 groups and\u00a0were sent to the North West Frontier Province. The groups of soldiers were posted at Samana Hills, Kurag, Sangar, Sahtop Dhar, and Saragarhi. A group of 21 soldiers of the 36th Regiment, led by\u00a0Ishar Singh, was posted at\u00a0Saragarhi. A small village in the border district of Kohat, Saragahi, was a modest location as it connected\u00a0Fort Lockhart\u00a0and Fort Gulistan. Being the common link of communication between all the three posts, it was a target of the Afghans and Orakzai tribesmen.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_18732\" style=\"width: 760px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-On-Map.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18732\" class=\"size-full wp-image-18732\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-On-Map.jpg\" alt=\"Saragarhi On Map\" width=\"750\" height=\"336\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-On-Map.jpg 750w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-On-Map-300x134.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18732\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Saragarhi On Map<\/p><\/div>\n<p>On 12 September 1897, a signalman of the regiment, Gurmukh Singh, warned Lieutenant Colonel John Haughton about the Afghans (more than 10,000) moving towards the Fort Lockhart. Haughton was unable to do anything in that situation and could not send any additional forces.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_18735\" style=\"width: 580px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18735\" class=\" wp-image-18735\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers.jpg\" alt=\"The 36th Sikhs Regiment Soldiers\" width=\"570\" height=\"339\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers.jpg 672w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-36th-Sikhs-Regiment-Soldiers-300x179.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18735\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The 36th Sikhs Regiment Soldiers<\/p><\/div>\n<p>At this point, the leader Ishar Singh and his men decided not to retreat and decided to fight<b> <\/b>\u201cBattle of Saragarhi\u201d to death. During this battle, around 200 Afghans were killed by these 21 soldiers who fought with great zeal and enthusiasm.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_18739\" style=\"width: 569px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Battle-Of-Saragarhi.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18739\" class=\" wp-image-18739\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Battle-Of-Saragarhi.jpg\" alt=\"Battle Of Saragarhi\" width=\"559\" height=\"354\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Battle-Of-Saragarhi.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Battle-Of-Saragarhi-300x190.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Battle-Of-Saragarhi-768x487.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 559px) 100vw, 559px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18739\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Battle Of Saragarhi<\/p><\/div>\n<p>The\u00a0grievously injured soldiers fought for 8 long hours without any break. When they were out of bullets and shells, they\u00a0engaged in\u00a0hand-to-hand combat. Their sacrifice did not go in vain as eventually, the enemies were defeated.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_18737\" style=\"width: 570px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Havildar-Ishar-Singh-With-His-Troops.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18737\" class=\"size-full wp-image-18737\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Havildar-Ishar-Singh-With-His-Troops.jpg\" alt=\"Havildar Ishar Singh With His Troops\" width=\"560\" height=\"480\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Havildar-Ishar-Singh-With-His-Troops.jpg 560w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Havildar-Ishar-Singh-With-His-Troops-300x257.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18737\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Havildar Ishar Singh With His Troops<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_18740\" style=\"width: 650px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-Ruins-Of-Saragarhi.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18740\" class=\"size-full wp-image-18740\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-Ruins-Of-Saragarhi.jpg\" alt=\"The Ruins Of Saragarhi\" width=\"640\" height=\"422\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-Ruins-Of-Saragarhi.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/The-Ruins-Of-Saragarhi-300x198.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18740\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The Ruins Of Saragarhi<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Awards\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Awards<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Indian Order of Merit Class III<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Death\"><\/span><span id=\"Death\" class=\"ez-toc-section\" style=\"color: #800080;\">Death<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>On 12 September 1897, Ishar Singh martyred after fighting the \u201cBattle of Saragarhi\u201d at Tirah, North-West Frontier Province, British India(now Pakistan).<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Facts\"><\/span><span id=\"Facts\" class=\"ez-toc-section\" style=\"color: #800080;\">Facts<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>British historian Major General James Lunt said that Ishar Singh was a somewhat turbulent character whose independent nature had brought him more than once into conflict with his military superiors. Thus, Ishar Singh \u2014in camp, a nuisance, in the field magnificent.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In order to honor the 21 Sikh soldiers of the 36th Sikh Regiment, two Saragarhi Memorial Gurudwaras were made in Ferozepur and Amritsar.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div id=\"attachment_18743\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Amritsar-left-and-Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Ferozepur-right.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18743\" class=\"size-full wp-image-18743\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Amritsar-left-and-Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Ferozepur-right.jpg\" alt=\"Saragarhi Memorial Gurudwara Amritsar (left) and Saragarhi Memorial Gurudwara Ferozepur (right)\" width=\"1024\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Amritsar-left-and-Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Ferozepur-right.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Amritsar-left-and-Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Ferozepur-right-300x101.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Amritsar-left-and-Saragarhi-Memorial-Gurudwara-Ferozepur-right-768x259.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18743\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Saragarhi Memorial Gurudwara Amritsar (left) and Saragarhi Memorial Gurudwara Ferozepur (right)<\/p><\/div>\n<ul>\n<li>As a tribute to the 21 brave Sikh soldiers, 12 September is celebrated as the \u201cSaragarhi Day.\u201d<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>After his martyrdom, none of his family members joined the army.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Numerous biopics have been made on Havildar Ishar Singh but \u2018Kesari\u2019 (2019), where Akshay Kumar portrayed his role has been the most famous film and has been able to grab the attention of the masses to the real heroes.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div id=\"attachment_18742\" style=\"width: 650px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Akshay-Kumar-in-Kesari.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18742\" class=\"size-full wp-image-18742\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Akshay-Kumar-in-Kesari.jpg\" alt=\"Akshay Kumar in Kesari\" width=\"640\" height=\"359\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Akshay-Kumar-in-Kesari.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Akshay-Kumar-in-Kesari-300x168.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18742\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Akshay Kumar in Kesari<\/p><\/div>\n<ul>\n<li>He is often confused with Captain Isher Singh, a soldier in the British Indian Army.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>After Havildar Ishar Singh\u2019s death, his brother killed his wife and got imprisoned at Kala Pani (Andaman and Nicobar).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Havildar Ishar Singh remains an iconic personality for his absolute bravery during the &#8220;Battle of Saragarhi,&#8221; and for being a true leader who would strive just for the comfort and safety of his own troop. Wiki\/Biography Havildar Ishar Singh was born into an agricultural family in Jagraon tehsil, Ludhiana district, Punjab.\u00a0He was married to Gurinderpal Singh Josan. Career Ishar Singh dreamt about becoming a soldier and got a chance to fulfill his dream by joining the Punjab Frontier Force at the age of 18 years. For the most part of his life, he remained on the battlefield under regimental number <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":24,"featured_media":18745,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[2],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/18717"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/24"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=18717"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/18717\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":20879,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/18717\/revisions\/20879"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/18745"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=18717"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=18717"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=18717"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}